  "extra_note_en": "Definite past (-dı) is used for events you personally witnessed or are sure about. Reported past (-miş) expresses hearsay, inference, surprise, or new discovery. Vowel harmony applies to both. Consonant change: -t after voiceless consonants (git-ti, bak-tı). Common time expressions: dün (yesterday), geçen hafta (last week), sabah (this morning), az önce (just now), 2020'de (in 2020), çocukken (when I was a child) for definite; and apparently, it seems, I heard that... for reported."
